### Grid Auto

Controls how the browser automatically places items that aren't explicitly positioned.

---

### Grid Auto Flow

```css
.container {
  grid-auto-flow: row;    /* Default - fill rows */
  grid-auto-flow: column; /* Fill columns */
  grid-auto-flow: dense;  /* Fill gaps aggressively */
}
```

---

### Grid Auto Rows / Columns

Controls size of **implicit** tracks (those not defined by `grid-template-*`):

```css
.container {
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  grid-auto-rows: 200px;  /* Any auto-created row = 200px */
  grid-auto-columns: 150px; /* Any auto-created column = 150px */
}
```

---

### Auto Flow: Row (Default)

```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  grid-auto-flow: row;
}
```

Items fill row by row, left to right, top to bottom.

---

### Auto Flow: Column

```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-auto-flow: column;
  grid-template-rows: repeat(3, 1fr);
}
```

Items fill column by column, top to bottom, left to right.

---

### Auto Flow: Dense

```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  grid-auto-flow: dense;
}
```

Fills empty gaps left by larger items. Items may not be in DOM order.

---

### Auto Placement Example

```css
/* 4 items in 3 column grid */
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  grid-auto-rows: 100px;
  gap: 10px;
}
```

Items 1-3 go in row 1. Item 4 goes in row 2 (implicit, 100px tall).

---

### Explicit vs Implicit Grid

| Grid Type | Defined By |
|-----------|-----------|
| **Explicit** | `grid-template-columns`, `grid-template-rows` |
| **Implicit** | Created automatically for items beyond the template |
| **Size** | `grid-auto-rows`, `grid-auto-columns` |

---

> **Key Point:** `grid-auto-flow: dense` can reduce whitespace but reorders items visually. Use with caution for content where order matters.
